Najer,E (2500)-Kron,V (2450) Moscow 1998 1-0 (39)}) 6... Qb6 7. e5 Nc6 8. Nd6+
Kf8 9. Bd3 Nge7 10. O-O h6 11. Kh1 a6 12. a3 Qc7 13. Be4 f5 14. Bxc6 dxc6 15.
Qxd4 c5 16. Qf2 b6 17. b4 c4 18. Qe2 Bd7 19. Nd4 Nd5 {Rendle,T (2393)-Zuse,K 
(2274) Gibraltar 2008 1-0}) (5. e5 d5 6. d4 cxd4 7. Nb5 Bf8 8. Bd3 (8. Nbxd4
Nc6 9. c3 a6 10. Be3 Nh6 11. Bd3 Nxd4 12. Bxd4 Be7 13. Qd2 Bd7 14. O-O Bb5 15.
Bxb5+ axb5 16. a3 Qc7 17. h3 Nf5 18. Qf2 h5 19. Rad1 h4 20. Rfe1 Rh5 21. Nh2
Ng3 22. Ng4 Ne4 {Lewtak,D (2340)-Wisniowska,K (2187) Krakow 2014 1/2-1/2}) 8...
Nc6 9. O-O Qb6 10. Kh1 Bd7 11. Qe1 Nb4 12. Nbxd4 Nxd3 13. cxd3 Rc8 14. Be3 Qxb2
15. Qh4 Be7 16. Qg3 h5 17. Rab1 Qxa2 18. Rxb7 Qa6 19. Rfb1 Qxd3 {Lanc,A (2344)
-Gazik,V (2291) Slovakia 2015 0-1 (67)}) (5. d4 $5 {must definitely be
considered} cxd4 6. Nxd4 $14) 5... Ne7 $11 6. d4 cxd4 7. Nxd4 a6 {Covers b5} (
7... O-O 8. e5 $11) 8. a4 (8. Be3 O-O $14) 8... O-O 9. O-O {Black has a
cramped position. Black's piece can't move: c8} (9. Bb3 d5 10. e5 Nbc6 $11)
9... Qb6 (9... d5 10. exd5 Nxd5 11. Bxd5 exd5 $11) 10. e5 {White gets more
space} (10. Be3 $142 {and White can hope to survive} Nbc6 11. e5 Nxd4 12. Bxd4
$11) 10... Nf5 $17 11. Nce2 d6 12. Kh1 Nxd4 (12... dxe5 13. Nxf5 exf5 14. Nc3
$17) 13. a5 Qc5 (13... Qc7 $5 14. Qxd4 dxe5 15. fxe5 Nc6 $17) 14. Qxd4 $15 Qxd4
15. Nxd4 dxe5 16. fxe5 Bxe5 17. c3 {Secures d4} Bd7 18. Bh6 (18. Rd1 Bxd4 19.
Rxd4 Bb5 20. Bxb5 axb5 $15) 18... Bg7 $17 19. Bg5 Nc6 20. Bf6 (20. Nf3 $5 $15)
20... Bxf6 $17 21. Rxf6 Kg7 22. Rf2 Nxd4 23. cxd4 Bc6 24. Rd1 Rad8 25. Rfd2 Rd6
26. d5 (26. Kg1 $5 $17) 26... exd5 27. Bxd5 $4 {the position was bad, and this
mistake simply hastens the end. .} (27. Kg1 $142 $19) 27... Rfd8 0-1

