{[%mdl 8192] A36: Symmetrical English vs ...g6: 4 Bg2 Bg7} 1. c4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6
3. g3 g6 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. e3 e6 6. Nge2 Nf6 7. d4 cxd4 8. exd4 (8. Nxd4 d5 (8...
a6 9. O-O O-O 10. Qe2 Qc7 11. Bd2 b6 12. Nxc6 dxc6 13. Rad1 Bb7 14. e4 Nd7 15.
f4 a5 16. e5 Rfd8 17. Ne4 Nc5 18. Nf6+ Kh8 19. b3 Nd7 20. Ne4 Nc5 21. Nd6 Bf8
22. Bc3 Kg8 23. Rd2 {Werner,C (2330)-Mueller,R (2190) Porto 2014 1-0 (37)}) 9.
Nxc6 bxc6 10. Qa4 Bd7 11. O-O O-O 12. Qc2 Ng4 13. b3 Qa5 14. Bd2 dxc4 15. h3
Ne5 16. f4 Nd3 17. Ne4 c3 18. Bxc3 Bxc3 19. Qxc3 Qxc3 20. Nxc3 Nb4 21. Ne4 Rfd8
22. Rfc1 Rab8 {Chernin,A (2583)-Ftacnik,L (2579) Austria 2000 1-0 (42)}) 8...
d5 9. cxd5 exd5 $146 (9... Nxd5 10. Nxd5 exd5 11. Qb3 O-O 12. Be3 Qa5+ 13. Qc3
Be6 14. Qxa5 Nxa5 15. b3 Rfd8 16. h4 Nc6 17. Kd2 Rac8 18. h5 Nb4 19. a3 Nc2 20.
Ra2 Nxe3 21. fxe3 Rc6 22. hxg6 fxg6 23. b4 Bf8 24. Nf4 {Lesiege,A (2375)-Madl,
I (2410) Budapest 1992 0-1 (60)}) (9... Nxd5 10. O-O $11) 10. O-O $14 O-O 11.
h3 {Controls g4} b6 (11... Re8 12. Re1 $11) 12. Nf4 {[%cal Rc3d5,Rf4d5,Rg2d5,
Gd8d5,Gf6d5] The pressure on the isolated pawn grows} (12. Bg5 Qd6 $16) 12...
Be6 (12... Bb7 13. Be3 $11) 13. Nxe6 {White forks: d8+f8} fxe6 {White has the
pair of bishops} 14. Re1 Ne4 {[%cal Rc6d4,Rg7d4,Gd1d4] Exerts pressure on the
isolated pawn} (14... Qd7 15. Be3 $14) 15. Nxe4 $16 dxe4 16. Rxe4 Bxd4 17. Rxd4
(17. Bf4 $142 Qf6 18. Qb3 $16) 17... Nxd4 $4 (17... Qxd4 $142 {was a good
chance to save the game} 18. Qxd4 Nxd4 19. Bxa8 Rxa8 $11) 18. Bxa8 $18 Qxa8 (
18... Qf6 19. Be3 Nf5 $18) 19. Qxd4 Rd8 (19... Qd5 {cannot change destiny} 20.
Qc3 Qd1+ 21. Kg2 $18) 20. Qg4 Qd5 21. Bg5 (21. Bh6 {keeps an even firmer grip}
b5 $18) 21... h5 22. Qf4 Rf8 23. Qd2 Rf5 24. h4 Qa8 (24... Qxd2 {does not
improve anything} 25. Bxd2 Rc5 26. Rc1 $18) 25. Rc1 (25. Qd7 {and White can
already relax} Qf3 26. Be3 Rd5 27. Qxa7 b5 $18) 25... Rd5 (25... Rf7 {doesn't
improve anything} 26. Qe2 Qd5 27. Rc8+ Rf8 28. Qc2 $18) 26. Qc2 (26. Qe3 $142 {
makes it even easier for White} Qe8 27. Qe4 $18) 26... Rc5 (26... Qe8 {
desperation} 27. Qe4 Kf7 $18) 27. Qxg6+ Kf8 28. Rxc5 bxc5 (28... Qb7 {a
fruitless try to alter the course of the game} 29. Qf6+ Kg8 30. Qxe6+ Kg7 31.
Qh6+ Kg8 32. Qg6+ Kh8 33. Rc8+ Qxc8 34. Bf6#) 29. Qf6+ Kg8 30. Qxe6+ Kg7 31.
Qe7+ Kg8 (31... Kg6 {does not save the day} 32. Qf6+ Kh7 33. Qf7+ Kh8 34. Bf6#)
32. Bh6 (32. Bh6 Qh1+ 33. Kxh1 a6 34. Qg7#) 1-0

