{[%mdl 8192] B20: Sicilian: Unusual White 2nd moves} 1. e4 c5 2. a3 d6 3. b4 b6
4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Bc4 Bg7 7. O-O $146 (7. bxc5 bxc5 8. e5 dxe5 9. Nxe5
Be6 10. Bxe6 fxe6 11. Qf3 Nbd7 12. Nxd7 Nxd7 13. O-O Rb8 14. Re1 Rb6 15. a4 Nf6
16. a5 Ra6 17. Qb7 Qd6 18. Nb5 Qc6 19. Qxa6 {1-0 (19) Chernyshov,K (2560)
-Tihonov,J (2500) Saratov 2006}) (7. bxc5 $5 Qc7 8. Qe2 bxc5 9. Nb5 $14) 7...
Bb7 8. e5 (8. Rb1 O-O (8... Nxe4 $143 9. Nxe4 Bxe4 10. Bxf7+ Kxf7 11. Ng5+ Kg8
12. Nxe4 $14) 9. d3 Nc6 $11) 8... dxe5 $11 9. Re1 {White threatens to win
material: Re1xe5} (9. Nxe5 O-O $11) 9... e4 $15 {Black threatens to win
material: e4xf3} 10. Ng5 {White threatens to win material: Ng5xe4. White forks:
e4+f7} O-O 11. Rb1 cxb4 12. axb4 Nbd7 (12... Qc7 $142 13. d3 exd3 14. Qxd3 Ng4
$17) 13. d4 $4 (13. Ngxe4 Ne5 14. Bb3 Rc8 $11) 13... exd3 $4 {releasing the
pressure on the opponent} (13... Qc7 $142 {Black missed this excellent chance}
14. Bxf7+ Rxf7 15. Nxf7 Qxc3 16. Nh6+ Kf8 $19) 14. Qxd3 $15 {Black has a
cramped position.} Nh5 15. Nce4 (15. Bb3 $142 $5 Ne5 16. Qe2 $15) 15... Ne5 $17
16. Qxd8 Raxd8 17. Bb3 h6 18. Nh3 (18. Nf3 Nxf3+ 19. gxf3 g5 $17) 18... Kh7 (
18... Bxe4 19. Bb2 Nf3+ 20. gxf3 Bxf3 21. Bxg7 Nxg7 22. Nf4 $19) 19. Nf4 (19.
f3 $142 $5 $17) 19... Bxe4 $19 20. Nxh5 gxh5 21. Bf4 $2 (21. Bb2 f5 22. f3 Bxf3
23. Bxe5 $19) 21... f5 22. f3 (22. Bxe5 {does not solve anything} Bxe5 23. f3
Bd4+ 24. Kh1 $19) 22... Nxf3+ (22... Ng6 $142 {it becomes clear that Black
will call all the shots} 23. fxe4 Nxf4 24. exf5 Rxf5 $19) 23. gxf3 $17 Bxf3 24.
Rxe7 Rfe8 25. Rxa7 (25. Rbe1 Bc6 $17) 25... Re4 $19 26. Bg3 (26. Bc1 $142 Rg4+
27. Kf2 $19) 26... h4 27. Be1 Kg6 28. c3 (28. h3 Bd4+ 29. Kf1 Be2+ 30. Kg2 $19)
28... Rde8 $4 {instead of simply winning the game} (28... Be5 $142 $19 {
and Black wins}) 29. Bf7+ $16 Kf6 30. Bxe8 Rxe8 31. Bxh4+ Kg6 32. Kf2 {White
threatens to win material: Kf2xf3} (32. Bf2 $142 $16) 32... Be4 $4 (32... Bg4
$14) 33. Re7 $4 {spoils everything} (33. Rg1+ $142 {secures the win} Kh5 34.
Raxg7 (34. Rgxg7 $6 Kxh4 35. Rg6 Rc8 $18) 34... Kxh4 35. R7g6 $18) 33... Rxe7
$11 {Black wins a piece} 34. Bxe7 $4 {throws away the game} (34. Rg1+ $142 {
would be a reprieve} Kf7 35. Rxg7+ Kxg7 36. Bxe7 $11) 34... Bxb1 $19 35. b5 (
35. c4 {doesn't change anything anymore} f4 36. Kf3 Kf5 $19) 35... Bxc3 36. Ke3
(36. Bd6 {doesn't get the bull off the ice} Bd4+ 37. Ke2 Kg5 $19) 36... Ba5 (
36... Be5 $142 {might be the shorter path} 37. Bd8 Bxh2 38. Bh4 $19) 37. Kd4 (
37. Bd6 {is not the saving move} Ba2 $19) 37... Ba2 (37... f4 $142 {and Black
has prevailed} 38. Bh4 Bb4 39. Ke5 $19) 38. Bd8 Be6 39. Bc7 Bd7 40. Kc4 h5 (
40... Kg5 $142 {seems even better} 41. Kd3 $19) 41. h4 (41. Bf4 $19 {the last
chance for counterplay}) 41... f4 42. Bxf4 Kf5 43. Bg5 Ke4 44. Bd8 (44. Kb3 {
is still a small chance} Bxb5 45. Bf6 $19) 44... Be6# 0-1

