{[%mdl 8192] C42: Petroff Defence: 3 Nxe5 and unusual White 3rd moves} 1. e4 e5
2. Nf3 {White threatens to win material: Nf3xe5} Bd6 $146 (2... f6 3. d4 (3.
Nxe5 Qe7 4. Nf3 d5 5. d3 dxe4 6. dxe4 Qxe4+ 7. Be2 Nc6 8. O-O Bd7 9. Nc3 Qg6
10. Ng5 h5 11. Bd3 Bf5 12. Ne6 Bxd3 13. Nxc7+ Kf7 14. cxd3 Qg4 15. Qb3+ Kg6 16.
Qxb7 Rc8 17. Qxc6 Ne7 {Demchenko,A (2465)-Pravdiuk,V (2285) Krasnodar 2007 1-0}
) 3... d6 4. Bc4 Qe7 5. O-O Be6 6. Bxe6 Qxe6 7. Nc3 c6 8. d5 Qf7 9. a4 g6 10.
b3 c5 11. Nd2 Ne7 12. f4 exf4 13. Nc4 Nc8 14. Bxf4 Qd7 15. Qf3 a6 16. a5 Be7
17. Bh6 {Petrosian,D (2363)-Abedi,A (2221) Lahijan 2005 1-0}) (2... Bc5 3. Nxe5
d6 4. Nf3 Be6 5. d4 Bb6 6. Nc3 Nf6 7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O c5 9. d5 Bg4 10. Bf4 Re8
11. h3 Bxf3 12. Qxf3 Nbd7 13. Bxd6 Rc8 14. Bb5 c4 15. Bxd7 Qxd7 16. e5 Bd4 17.
Rfe1 {Mihalichenko,V (2407)-Tikhiy,S (2427) Azov 2010 1-0}) (2... h6 3. Bc4 Qf6
4. O-O d6 5. h3 Be6 6. Bxe6 Qxe6 7. Nc3 Nf6 8. d4 Be7 9. d5 Qd7 10. Be3 b5 11.
Qd3 a6 12. Ne2 O-O 13. Ng3 {1/2-1/2 (13) Bujnoch,R (2233)-Svanda,P (2198)
Czechia 2009}) (2... Nc6 3. Bb5 $11) 3. Bc4 Nf6 {Black threatens to win
material: Nf6xe4} 4. O-O c6 $2 {Prevents intrusion on b5+d5} (4... Nc6 $5 $14 {
should be considered}) 5. Re1 (5. d4 Qc7 $16) 5... b5 (5... c5 6. d4 $1 {
forging ahead of the opponent} cxd4 7. Nxd4 $16) 6. Bb3 h6 (6... Bc7 7. d4 d6
8. a4 $16) 7. c3 (7. d4 Bc7 8. dxe5 Ng4 $18) 7... Na6 (7... Bc7 $5 $16) 8. d4
$18 exd4 $4 {the pressure is too much, Black crumbles} (8... Qc7 $142 $18) 9.
e5 O-O 10. cxd4 (10. exd6 $5 {keeps an even firmer grip} dxc3 11. Nxc3 Nc5 $18)
10... Bb4 11. Bd2 (11. exf6 $142 {ends the debate} Bxe1 12. fxg7 (12. Qxe1 $6
Qxf6 13. Be3 Bb7 $18) (12. Nxe1 $6 Qxf6 13. Nc3 Re8 $18) 12... Bxf2+ 13. Kxf2
Kxg7 14. a4 bxa4 15. Rxa4 $18) 11... Nd5 12. Nc3 d6 (12... Bb7 $5 $16) 13. Nxd5
$18 c5 $4 {Black falls apart} (13... cxd5 14. Bxb4 Nxb4 $18) 14. Nxb4 cxb4 15.
Bd5 (15. Qc2 $5 {might be the shorter path} d5 $18) 15... Rb8 16. Qb3 Qa5 (
16... Bb7 $18 {praying for a miracle}) 17. exd6 Bd7 18. Ne5 Rbd8 19. Nxf7 (19.
Bxf7+ Rxf7 20. Qxf7+ Kh8 21. Ng6+ Kh7 22. Re7 Rg8 23. Nf8+ Kh8 24. Bxh6 Qxa2
25. Bxg7+ Rxg7 26. Qxg7#) 19... Kh7 20. Qd3+ g6 (20... Bf5 {cannot change what
is in store for White} 21. Qxf5+ g6 22. Ng5+ hxg5 23. Re7+ Rf7 24. Qxf7+ Kh8
25. Qf6#) 21. Re7 Rde8 (21... Kg7 {doesn't get the cat off the tree} 22. Ne5+
Rf7 23. Qxg6+ Kh8 24. Nxf7#) 22. Rxd7 (22. Rxd7 Re1+ 23. Rxe1 Qc7 24. Ne5+ Qxd7
25. Qxg6+ Kh8 26. Qxh6+ Qh7 27. Ng6#) (22. Ng5+ Kh8 23. Rh7#) 1-0

