Qxf5 {Lazarevic,M (2160)-Kozlovskaya,V (2262) Cheliabinsk 2005 1/2-1/2 (36)}) (
10. a4 Ng4 $11) 10... Qc7 (10... exf5 $5 11. exf5 Re8 $17) 11. fxe6 $11 fxe6
12. Ng5 {White threatens to win material: Ng5xe6} Bd7 13. Qh4 h6 {Black
threatens to win material: h6xg5} 14. Nf3 e5 (14... b5 15. a3 $15) 15. Bxh6 $11
gxh6 16. Qxh6 {Black wins a piece} Rf7 17. Ng5 {White threatens to win
material: Ng5xf7} Bf8 $4 {makes life more difficult} (17... Rg7 $142 {this is
the best bet to save the position} 18. Rxf6 Bxf6 19. Qxf6 Rf8 $11) 18. Qg6+ (
18. Qh4 Bc6 19. Nxf7 Bg7 20. Nh6+ Bxh6 21. Qxh6 Nh7 $18) 18... Rg7 19. Qxf6 (
19. Rxf6 $142 {seems even better} Rxg6 20. Rxg6+ Bg7 $18) 19... Be7 20. Ne6
Bxf6 21. Nxc7 Rf8 22. N7d5 Bd8 23. Rxf8+ Kxf8 24. Rf1+ Rf7 25. b3 Ba5 (25... b5
26. Ne3 $18) 26. a4 Bc6 (26... a6 27. Nd1 $18) 27. Nb5 Bxd5 (27... Bxb5 {
does not win a prize} 28. axb5 Rxf1+ 29. Kxf1 $18) 28. exd5 Bb6 (28... Rxf1+ {
does not help much} 29. Kxf1 Ke7 30. Nxa7 Bd8 $18) 29. Nxd6 (29. Rxf7+ {
keeps an even firmer grip} Kxf7 30. Nxd6+ Kf8 $18) 29... Rxf1+ (29... c4+ $142
{and Black wins} 30. Rf2 cxd3 31. cxd3 Rxf2 $19) 30. Kxf1 $18 Ke7 (30... a6 {
doesn't change the outcome of the game} 31. Nxb7 Ke7 32. h4 $18) 31. Nc4 (31.
Nc8+ {and White can already relax} Kf8 32. Nxb6 Kf7 $18) 31... Bc7 (31... Bd8
$18 {no good, but what else?}) 32. d6+ Bxd6 33. Nxd6 Kxd6 34. h4 Ke6 35. h5 Kf7
36. Ke2 Kf6 37. g4 Kg5 38. Ke3 Kxg4 39. h6 Kg5 1-0

