N6d7 6. exd6 cxd6 7. d4 g6 8. Nf3 Bg7 9. Be2 O-O 10. O-O Nc6 11. d5 Nxa5 12.
Bd2 b6 13. Bc3 Ne5 14. Nd4 Bd7 15. b3 g5 16. Nd2 Nb7 17. N2f3 h6 18. Nxe5 Bxe5
{Firman,N (2511)-Neverov,V (2564) Ordzhonikidze 2001 0-1 (62)}) 4... g6 $146 (
4... e6 5. Nf3 d6 6. exd6 cxd6 7. Bd3 Be7 8. O-O Nc6 9. a3 Bf6 10. Be3 Bd7 11.
Nc3 O-O 12. Rc1 e5 13. d5 Ne7 14. Qc2 Ng6 15. b4 Bg4 16. Nd2 Be7 17. f3 Bc8 18.
Qa2 a5 19. Qc2 {Al Subaihi,K (2174)-Osman,G (2185) Sanaa 2002 1-0 (35)}) (4...
d6 5. exd6 exd6 6. Nf3 $11) 5. Nf3 (5. c5 Nd5 6. Bc4 c6 $16) 5... e6 $2 (5...
d6 $142 $5 $11 {looks like a viable alternative}) 6. Bd3 d6 7. O-O N8d7 (7...
Nc6 8. Nc3 $16) 8. Bg5 (8. Qe2 Bg7 $16) 8... Be7 $16 9. Bh6 (9. Bxe7 $5 Qxe7
10. exd6 cxd6 11. a4 $16) 9... dxe5 $14 10. Bg7 {White threatens to win
material: Bg7xh8. White forks: e5+h8} Rg8 11. Bxe5 Nxe5 12. dxe5 {Black has
the pair of bishops.} Bd7 (12... g5 13. Qe2 g4 14. Nfd2 $14) 13. Nc3 $16 a6 14.
Re1 Bb4 15. Qd2 {White has a very active position} (15. Be4 c6 $16) 15... Qe7
$14 16. a3 Bc5 $4 (16... Bxc3 $142 {would hold out} 17. Qxc3 O-O-O $14) 17. b4
$18 O-O-O (17... Nxc4 {does not save the day} 18. Bxc4 Bb6 19. Ne4 $18) 18.
bxc5 Qxc5 19. Ne4 Qe7 (19... Qf8 {doesn't get the bull off the ice} 20. Nd4 Be8
21. c5 Rxd4 22. cxb6 $18) 20. Qb4 (20. c5 $142 {and the rest is a matter of
technique} Bb5 21. Nd6+ cxd6 22. exd6 Rxd6 23. cxd6 Qxd6 24. Qc1+ Kb8 25. Bxb5
axb5 $18) 20... Qf8 (20... Qxb4 {is one last hope} 21. axb4 Bc6 $18) 21. Qxf8 (
21. Qxf8 Rgxf8 22. Nc5 $18) 1-0

