Rg1 Nd4 15. c3 Nxf3+ 16. Nxf3 f5 17. g4 fxg4 18. hxg4 Bg6 19. Rg3 O-O 20. Kg2
c4 {Mossong,H (2184)-Mueller,O (2311) Khanty-Mansiysk 2010 0-1 (39)}) 6... Bd6
7. Nf3 Bg4 8. h3 Bxf3 9. Qxf3 Qh4+ 10. g3 Qe7 11. a4 Nf6 12. a5 Nd7 13. Bd2 c4
14. dxc4 exf4 15. gxf4 Bb4 16. Rg1 O-O-O 17. O-O-O Qc5 18. Rxg7 Qxa5 19. Nb1
Nb6 20. Bxb4 {Marholev,D (2418)-Villa Izquierdo,R (2195) Lyon 2006 1-0 (38)}) (
5... e5 6. f4 exf4 7. Bxf4 $11) 6. f4 (6. Nf3 Bg7 $14) 6... Bg7 7. Nf3 b5 (7...
Bg4 8. h3 Bxf3 9. Qxf3 $14) 8. O-O $14 b4 {Black wins space} (8... Bd4+ 9. Kh1
$16) 9. Na4 $16 Bg4 10. e5 Qd4+ $2 (10... c4 11. dxc4 Qxd1 12. Rxd1 $16) 11.
Kh1 (11. Nxd4 $5 {keeps an even firmer grip} Bxd1 12. Nxc5 Bg4 $18) 11... Bxf3
(11... Qd8 12. h3 Bc8 13. Be3 $18) 12. Qxf3 $18 (12. gxf3 $6 Nh6 $14) 12... Rc8
(12... Qd5 13. Qf2 Rd8 14. Nxc5 $18) 13. Nb6 Rc7 14. c3 bxc3 (14... Qd8 15. f5
f6 16. e6 $18) 15. bxc3 Qxc3 (15... Qd8 16. Rb1 $18) 16. Rb1 Nh6 (16... Qd4 {
doesn't improve anything} 17. Be3 Qd8 $18) 17. Na8 (17. Nd5 $142 {and White
wins} cxd5 18. Rb8+ Rc8 19. Rxc8+ Kd7 20. Rxh8 Bxh8 21. Qxd5+ Ke8 22. Qa8+ Kd7
23. Qb7+ Kd8 24. Be3 $18) 17... Rc8 $16 18. Nc7+ $4 {not a good decision,
because now the opponent is right back in the game} (18. Rb3 $142 Qa5 19. Nb6
$16) 18... Rxc7 $19 19. Rb8+ (19. f5 Nxf5 20. g4 e6 21. gxf5 exf5 (21... Qxe5
$2 {fails to} 22. Bf4 Qxf5 23. Bxc7 $18) (21... Bxe5 22. Bb2 Qxb2 23. Rxb2 Bxb2
24. Qg3 $18) (21... gxf5 $6 22. Rg1 Bxe5 23. Bb2 Qxb2 24. Rxb2 Bxb2 25. Rb1 $17
) 22. Rb8+ Ke7 $19) 19... Kd7 20. Rb3 (20. Bb2 Qc2 21. Rxh8 Bxh8 22. e6+ fxe6
23. Bxh8 $19) 20... Qd4 $4 {a weak move, ruining a winning position} (20... Qa5
$142 {secures the point} 21. Ra3 Qb5 $19) 21. Bb2 $16 Qd5 22. e6+ $1 {
Discovered attack: e5, Bb2xg7} Qxe6 $2 (22... Qxe6 23. Bxg7 {Discovered attack}
) (22... Kxe6 23. Re1+ {Decoy Double attack} (23. Bxg7 {Discovered attack})) (
22... fxe6 23. Bxg7 {Discovered attack}) 23. Bxg7 $18 Rg8 (23... Rd8 24. Bxh6
Ke8 25. Qf2 $18) 24. Bxh6 f6 25. Qe4 {[%cal Yf4f5] White prepares f5} (25. Qf2
{seems even better} Qf5 26. Rc1 Qh5 27. Rxc5 Qd1+ 28. Qg1 Qxg1+ 29. Kxg1 Rd8
$18) 25... Qg4 $2 (25... Qxe4 26. dxe4 Rd8 27. f5 $18) 26. f5 (26. Re1 $142 $5
{and White can already relax} Re8 $18) 26... gxf5 27. Qxf5+ Qxf5 28. Rxf5 Ke6 (
28... c4 29. dxc4 Rg4 30. Rf4 Rxf4 31. Bxf4 $18) 29. Rxc5 Rg4 30. h3 (30. Ra5 {
might be the shorter path} Kf7 $18) 30... Ra4 31. Bf4 {White threatens to win
material: Bf4xc7} (31. a3 $142 $18 {secures victory}) 31... Rxf4 $11 32. Rb6 {
[%cal Rb6c6,Rc5c6,Gc7c6] The isolani on c6 becomes a target. White threatens
to win material: Rb6xa6. White forks: a6+c6} (32. Rh5 Rf1+ 33. Kh2 Rf2 $11)
32... Kd6 $15 {Black threatens to win material: Kd6xc5} 33. Ra5 {White
threatens to win material: Ra5xa6} Rd4 {Black threatens to win material: Rd4xd3
} 34. Ra3 Ra7 35. Rc3 {White threatens to win material: Rc3xc6} Rc7 36. Rxa6
Rd5 37. Ra8 h5 38. Rd8+ Rd7 {Black threatens to win material: Rd7xd8} 39. Rc8 {
White threatens to win material: Rc8xc6} (39. Rxd7+ Kxd7 40. a4 Re5 $11) 39...
Rc5 $15 {Black threatens to win material: Rc5xc3} 40. Rb3 Kd5 41. Rcb8 Kd4 42.
R8b4+ Kd5 43. a4 (43. Rb8 e5 $15) 43... Ra7 44. Ra3 Raa5 45. Rh4 {White
threatens to win material: Rh4xh5} Kd6 46. Rd4+ Rd5 {Black threatens to win
material: Rd5xd4} 47. Rc4 c5 48. Rh4 Rd4 {[%cal Ra5a4,Rd4a4,Ga3a4] Attacking
the isolated pawn on a4} 49. Rxd4+ cxd4 50. Kg1 (50. Ra1 Kc5 51. g4 hxg4 52.
hxg4 Kb4 $15) 50... Kc5 $17 51. Ra2 (51. Ra1 Kb4 52. Kf2 Rxa4 $17) 51... Kb4
52. Kf2 Rxa4 (52... Kb3 $142 53. Ra1 Kb2 $19) 53. Rxa4+ $4 {causes further
problems for White} (53. Rc2 $142 $17) 53... Kxa4 $19 54. Kf3 Kb4 55. g4 (55.
h4 {there is nothing else anyway} f5 56. Kf4 $19) 55... h4 56. Kf4 Kc3 57. Ke4
e5 (57... e6 $142 {finishes off the opponent} 58. Kf3 Kxd3 $19) 58. Kf5 Kxd3
59. Kxf6 Ke4 (59... e4 $142 {and Black has triumphed} 60. g5 e3 61. g6 $19) 60.
g5 d3 61. g6 d2 62. g7 d1=Q 63. g8=Q Qf1+ 64. Ke7 Qxh3 $4 {overlooking an easy
win} (64... Ke3 $142 $19 {and the result of the game is clear: Black will win})
65. Qc4+ $11 Kf3 66. Qf7+ $4 {White lets it slip away} (66. Qb3+ Kg2 67. Qb2+
Kg3 68. Qc3+ Kh2 69. Qxe5+ Qg3 70. Qe2+ Kh3 $19) 66... Kg3 $4 {an unfortunate
move that relinquishes the win} (66... Kg2 {makes it even easier for Black} 67.
Qa2+ Kg3 68. Qb3+ Kh2 69. Qb2+ Qg2 70. Qxe5+ Qg3 71. Qe2+ Kh3 72. Qe4 $19) 67.
Qg7+ $4 {throwing away the advantage} (67. Qb3+ Kh2 68. Qb2+ Qg2 69. Qxe5+ Qg3
70. Qe2+ Kh3 71. Qe4 $19) 67... Qg4 68. Qxe5+ Kh3 69. Qe3+ Qg3 70. Qe6+ Kg2 71.
Qe2+ Qf2 72. Qe4+ Kf1 73. Qb1+ (73. Kd7 $19) 73... Qe1+ 74. Qxe1+ Kxe1 0-1

